    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1600"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1600">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.62/107.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">German-Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                        calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1914-11-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                        notBefore="1914-10-28T00:00:00-05:00">undated</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">memorandum</hi>.</p>
                <p>The German Legation at Mexico reports under October 28th: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>The German Vice Consul at Guanajuato is proprietor of a valuable estate
                            [“hacienda “] named Santiago in the State of Zacatecas, County
                            [“Partido.”] of Villanueva. After seizure of this estate by the Mexicon
                            Constitutionalists the restitution was reclaimed without any result. By
                            order of Francisco Villa the estate has now been confiscated according
                            to the enclosed order. The restitution has been reclaimed at Mexico
                            again on October 23rd.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure—Translation.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Constitutionalist Army, <lb/> Division of the
                                    North</hi>
                            </placeName>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Col. Miguel Hernandez, in a telephone message to-day tells me: <quote
                            rend="blockquote">
                            <p>General Francisco Villa orders me: Inform the ranches “Encarnacion,”
                                “Tayanua,” “Salto,” “Santiago “and any others along that route which
                                are confiscated, that from this moment they are absolutely
                                prohibited from taking away corn, stock, or anything, even though
                                they may have an order of the Department of Agriculture, until a new
                                order has been given. Please convey as quickly as possible this
                                order to the managers of these properties. This I communicate to you
                                for your information and due performance.</p>
                        </quote>
                    </p>
                    <closer>
                        <dateline rendition="#left">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Villanueva</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-13">
                                <hi rend="italic">October 13, 1914</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                        <lb/> First Captain, Chief of Arms, <lb/>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">R. S. Garay</hi>
                        </signed>. <lb/>
                        <dateline rendition="#left">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">German Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-07">
                                <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1914</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
